	<pb n="0001" facs="liv_002063_0001"><!--pb/@n='76r'--></pb>
<lb/><p rend="right"><placeName><settlement type="town">Hamilton</settlement></placeName> <date when="1864-09-06">6 <choice><abbr>Sept<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi></abbr><expan>September</expan></choice>
<lb/>1864</date></p>
<lb/><p>My Dear <persName>Waller</persName></p>
<lb/><p>Thanking you
<lb/>for your note <space dim="horizontal" extent="1" unit="words"/>of
<lb/>Saturday. I am to be at
<lb/>a <persName>D<hi rend="sup underline">r</hi> Watson</persName>'s at
<lb/><placeName><settlement type="town">Bath</settlement></placeName>. He is a friend
<lb/>of <persName>Sir Boderick</persName> &amp;
<lb/>I agreed to accept his
<lb/>hospitality a good while
<lb/>ago. A cold shiver
<lb/>comes over me when
<lb/>I think of my speech
<lb/>at which I am labouring
<lb/>with (figuratively) coat
<lb/>off &amp; sleeves tucked up
    
	

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_002063_0002"><!--pb/@n='76v'--></pb>
<lb/>I mean to give my
<lb/>time to a publication
<lb/>immediately after <placeName><settlement type="town">Bath</settlement></placeName>
<lb/>but not <hi rend="underline">con amore</hi>.
<lb/>I did write to
<lb/><persName>Mackenzie</persName> I believe
<lb/>twice since I came
<lb/>home.</p><!-- There is a curved bracket around lines 5-8 with the word "omit" written in the margin of letter HB 9/25/12 -->
<lb/><p>I had a splendid time
<lb/>in the <placeName><region>Highlands</region></placeName> to
<lb/>visit my ancestral
<lb/>islet <placeName><geogName type="feature"><unclear>Ulla</unclear></geogName></placeName>. The
<lb/>Highlanders cheered me
<lb/>as "a man &amp; a brother"
<lb/>and gave me a free
<lb/>ticket "at anytime, to
<lb/>&amp; from any place"
<lb/><choice><abbr>compts</abbr><expan>compliments</expan></choice> to <persName>Chimwala</persName>

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_002063_0003"><!--pb/@n='77r'--></pb>
<lb/>and tell him I had capital
<lb/>"Jigging" We killed
<lb/>eleven salmon in one
<lb/>forenoon. Have your
<lb/>handkerchief ready
<lb/>when you read this,
<lb/>and believe me
<lb/><choice><sic>whats</sic><corr>what's</corr></choice> bred in the
<lb/>bone <choice><sic>wont</sic><corr>won't</corr></choice> come
<lb/>out of the flesh</p>
<lb/><p rend="center"><persName><choice><abbr>D.L.</abbr><expan>David Livingstone</expan></choice></persName></p><!-- Appears to be writing in bottom left corner of page, along with <persName><choice><abbr>D<hi rend="sup;ul">r</hi></abbr><expan>Doctor</expan><choice><abbr>L.</abbr><expan>Livingstone</expan> written perpendicular to text in bottom right corner HB 9/25/12-->

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_002063_0004"><!--pb/@n='77v'--></pb><!-- This page contains no text, but bleedthrough from recto side evident HB 9/25/12 -->
			
